f35eac95-2271-4bf2-bfa6-c83aca2f1b28.body: Frequently Asked QuestionsIf I sign up for Realogy Military Rewards^&, am I obligated to use the program? No, your personal Advocate will happily explain the program details without any obligation.Is it free to register for the program?Yes, there is no cost to sign up!Are there hidden costs to this program after I sign up? No, there are no hidden costs! When you buy or sell a home through our program, the real estate company splits their commission with us. This commission split is a common practice in the real estate industry and is used to increase business for the broker and provide a savings to homebuyers and sellers. How long will it take for an agent to contact me?You will be contacted by phone within one business day.Can I pick the agent that I would like to work with?Realogy Military Rewards^& connects you with a qualified agent who is affiliated with our brands, all of whom have a 96% satisfaction rating or better. These agents are from the most recognized real estate brands, including Better Homes and Gardens Real Estate, Century 21, Coldwell Banker, ERA Real Estate, and Corcoran. If for any reason you are not satisfied with your agent, your Realogy Military Rewards^& Advocate can assist and request another agent.Who is Realogy?Realogy Holdings Corp. is the largest full service residential real estate services company in the United States. With well known and trusted brands including: Better Homes and Gardens Real Estate, Coldwell Banker, Century 21, ERA Real Estate, and Corcoran.Who is PCSgrades?PCSgrades is a community of fellow military members, veterans, and spouses helping each other with their biggest must-solve relocation needs including trusted insights and reviews for off-base neighborhoods, base housing, moving companies, schools, and more.What is Shyft?Shyft is an added Realogy Military Rewards service that offers a simple way to move. You will be connected with a move coach that will help you throughout the entire process. Realogy Military Rewards is not involved in the moving of household goods but will be able to give you all of the information to get started once you enroll in the real estate program.
